Place butter in a 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking pan; place in a 350 degrees F oven until melted. Remove from the oven. Sprinkle the cracker crumbs evenly over butter. Pour milk evenly over crumbs. Sprinkle with chips; press down firmly. Bake at 350 degrees F for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack before cutting.